<li id="cite_note-chopra130-82"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-chopra130_82-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-chopra130_82-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Chopra <i>et al.</i>, p 130</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-milinda-83"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-milinda_83-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The Buddhist work <i>Milinda Panha</i> dated to the early Christian era, mentions Kolapttna among the best-known sea ports on the Chola coast. Nilakanta Sastri, <i>The CōĻas</i>, p 23</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-Nagaswamy-84"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Nagaswamy_84-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Nagaswamy, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://tamilartsacademy.com/books/coins/cover.html"><i>Tamil Coins – a study</i></a></span></li>
