<li id="cite_note-unity-87"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-unity_87-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The only other time when peninsular India would be brought under one umbrella before the <a href="History_of_the_Republic_of_India" title="History of the Republic of India">Independence</a> was during the <a href="Vijayanagara_Empire" title="Vijayanagara Empire">Vijayanagara Empire</a> (1336–1614)</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-88"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-88">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Stein, p 26</span></li>
